{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3487472,"name":"Kevin ","username":"kr1699","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/kr1699/{size}/207533_2.png","created_at":"2025-01-19T16:29:50.149Z","cooked":"<p>We are trying to integrate photonvision with the ctre autogenerated swerve. We’ve created the photon pose estimator and are attempting to feed it from our camera, using the 2024 field map and 2024 speaker since we still have it assembled. It returns the same exact pose every tick for each tag. I’ve driven sideways, forwards and backwards, and rotated, with nothing changing.<br>
<img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/9/0933f0246ea0c63a108a731c8cd7fe645f61411c.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="1jpzAtC08f8aA6PgDHr6mjCK1Fq" width="271" height="152"></p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">var latestResults = camera.getAllUnreadResults();
for(PhotonPipelineResult result : latestResults) {
   Optional&lt;EstimatedRobotPose&gt; poseData = visionEstimator.update(result);
   if (poseData.isPresent()) {
      EstimatedRobotPose estimatedPose = poseData.get();
      System.out.println("processing pose at " + estimatedPose.timestampSeconds);
      System.out.println(estimatedPose.estimatedPose.toPose2d());
      addVisionMeasurement(estimatedPose.estimatedPose.toPose2d(), estimatedPose.timestampSeconds);
   }
}
</code></pre>
